# CI Workflow Triggers

## Build & Test (`.github/workflows/build.yml`)

| Event | Native builds | Tests |
|---|---|---|
| **PR → `main`** | quality → debug compile → test (sequential) | DinD + coturn |
| **Push → `main`** | full release matrix, then test | yes |
| Other branches | no | no |

PR pipeline order: **typecheck → lint → debug compile → integration tests**. Quality uses workspace `npm ci` only (no registry packages, no `.node`).

Release tags run **real `npm publish`** (not dry-run); version is taken from the tag (`release/x.y.z` → `x.y.z`).

## Release (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)

Runs **only** on `release/*` tag push: full **release** matrix build → test (DinD) → npm publish → GitHub Release.

```bash
git checkout main && git pull
git tag release/0.1.0 && git push origin release/0.1.0
```

Local alternatives: `scripts/release-local.sh` and `scripts/release-publish.sh`. See `scripts/RELEASE.md`.

## CI Docker image (`ci` branch)

Rebuild `ghcr.io/.../ci-build:latest` when `docker/ci/Dockerfile` changes — push to **`ci`** branch or **`workflow_dispatch`** on CI Docker image workflow.

## Caching (`.github/workflows/build.yml`)

- **`changes` job** (`dorny/paths-filter`): `native`, `typescript`, `workflows`.
- **PR `build-pr`**: debug `.node` cache (`profile: debug`); skip compile when native unchanged and cache hits.
- **Main `build-linux` / `build-host`**: release `.node` cache (`profile: release`); always compile on main push.
- **`Swatinem/rust-cache`**: separate prefix keys for PR debug vs main release.
- **Test job**: `docker:24-dind` service on `ubuntu-latest` (no job container — avoids checkout/DNS failures with `DOCKER_HOST`); tests run in `ci-build` with coturn sharing network namespace.

## Local validation

```bash
npm run ci:verify:linux          # release cross-builds (matches main push)
npm run ci:verify:checks:docker  # PR test checks
npm run ci:verify                # both
```

After changing `docker/ci/Dockerfile`, rebuild (`npm run ci:docker:build`) and push to `ci` branch.
